<Author>pbaudit
<Content>Very Pleased with Barcelo Sants The Barcelo Sants is a transit friendly hotel, located above the Estacion Sants (Sants Station). The hotel is serviced by a train station, Metro and the Tourist Bus. It is a decent, standard hotel that is located about 2-3 miles from Las Rambles. The rooms were relatively large (for a European room - comparable to a standard US hotel room), with good air conditioning (important during the summer). Getting to the hotel from the Airport was very easy. The Airport train station is accessed via an overhead walkway between terminals A  B. The fare is 2.30 Euros. The train is very popular and there was a long line to buy tickets at the station (tip - use the automated ticket machines to the left - they accept credit cards and Euros). The train stops at Estacion Sants (2nd stop). You get out onto the platform and take the escalator (or elavator) to the station. Since we were going on a cruise, we had a lot of luggage. Fortunately, there is an open gate (to the left) that we used. The hotel entrance is a few steps from the open gate. You take a small elevator that goes up to the lobby.The hotel has a bar, restaurant, fitness center, and a Cyber area. I didn't eat that the restaurant, although it looked like they had a decent breakfast buffet for 12 Euros. The Fitness center (10 Euros) is very good with treadmills and other cardio equipment. It also has an ice machine (on the 2nd floor). There is a Super market (Hipermarket) at an adjacent corner to the hotel.Getting to other areas within Barcelona was very easy, taking Metro or the train. The station is service by 2 Metro lines (3  5). The Metro fares are reasonable 1.15 Euro per trip, or 10 trips for 6.50 Euros. Las Rambles was about a 10-15 minute metro ride.We stayed at the Bacelo Sants both for pre cruise and post curise. For both stays, we were able to check in early (12 noon and 10 am). We took a cab to/from the Cruise dock and were charged 16  10 Euros. Cab fares can vary greatly as, in addition to the metered rate, they are supposed to charge extra for each bag and a cruise port surcharge (2 Euro). We were fortunate as our drivers (to and from) the cruise ports neglected to charge us for some (or all) of the surcharges. Our friends, who were actually much closer to the port (near Las Rambles), paid 25 Euros for a cab. We were very pleased with our stay at the Barcelos Sants, especially when you consider our friends paid over 220 Euros for their hotel (near Las Rables) and we paid $100 via Priceline. Our friends complained that their hotel rooms were small, one had air conditioning problems, and wouldn't allow them to check in early. If you are not particular about staying in a specific area (i.e. Las Rambles), then I would highly recommend the Barcelo Sants 
