<Content>Good But not 4 star I had lived in Hotel Sants for 8 days. I stayed in a standard room so could not expect much.Few Things that I liked are:1) It is an economical place and good for people on a small budget.2) The reception staff was friendly and polite.3) Good bathroom and a very powerful shower.4) Very Good for people who want to travel around since It is connected to the Metro station and the other rail and bus stations.If you need a double bed ask for it.....and do not have breafast in the hotel. There is a McDonalds in the station or u can quickly venture into La Rambla for a nice and cheap brkfst.Yet most importantly, there is no pub or a good restaurant close to the restaurant so u need to ensure that u have ur food needs taken care of.A few more tips: La Rambla / Barri Gothic is the place to hang around.Buy a 10 trip travel card for euro 6 (cheap....very cheap option)Shop some frozen fish from Champion Supermarket to bring back home.And, visit BarcelonaCentral a Food Joint in the Boqueira Market at the La Rambla for some Good sea food...cooked and served hot!!! 
